        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "When the Lord cometh ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Armed with a power which they will be utterly unable to resist, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "What will he do unto these husbandmen — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Who had been so treacherous and cruel? With a view to their stronger conviction, he refers it to themselves to judge in this case. For God’s proceedings are so unexceptionable, there needs only an appeal to sinners themselves concerning the equity of them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "They say, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(for how could they with any decency say otherwise?) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He will miserably destroy these wicked men ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Κακους κακως απολεσει αυτους",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "he will put those wretches to a wretched death: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(So Campbell:) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and will let out his vineyard to other husbandmen. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thus, before they were aware, they condemned themselves, and signified that their privileges and blessings would be taken from them, the governors of their church and commonwealth destroyed, and the Gentiles taken to be God’s people in their stead: an interpretation of the parable which our Lord immediately confirmed, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 20:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; when they replied with apparent seriousness, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "God forbid.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
